provisions.content:
6. A company shall not be registered in a name which in the opinion of
the Registrar is undesirable having regard to the fact that-
      (a) whether in English or a foreign language, it-
              (i) is offensive;
             (ii) outrages public decency and morality;
            (iii) connotes an undertaking that is scandalous, obscene and
                  immoral: or
            (iv) contravenes the Govenunent's policy on security;
       (b) the use of the name would constitute a criminal offence.

9.-41) The use of certain words in a proposed company name which
refer to a profession, occupation, or other business or activity shall require
the production of certification from the relevant professional or regulatory
body upon submission for registration.
         (2) Words referred to in paragraph (1) include words such as-
         "Engineer";
         "Medical";
         "Dental";
         "Bank";
         "Cambio";
         "Pharmacy";
         "University"
